  "text": "Chemistry is one golden rule. Atoms cannot be created or destroyed. What goes in must come out. That's why we balance equations. Tick hydrogen plus oxygen makes water. H2 plus O2, arrow H2O. But count the oxygens. Two on the left, one on the right. That's not balanced. Fix it. Put a two in front of water. H2 plus O2, arrow two, H2O. Now oxygens match two each side. But hydrogens, two on the left, four on the right. So put a two in front of hydrogen. Two H2 plus O2, arrow two, H2O. Count again. Hydrogens, four and four. Oxygens, two and two. Balanced, here's the method. Step one, rate the unbalanced equation. Step two, pick the most complex molecule. Step three, balance one element at a time. Step four, leave hydrogen and oxygen for last. Step five, do a final count. The coefficients you put in front, those become your mole ratios. And mole ratios are everything in stoichiometry. That's the next video.",
